---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="about">
  <h1 class="font-display text-5xl font-bold lowercase tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
    about<span class="text-accent">.</span>
  </h1>

  <div class="mt-8 max-w-2xl space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
    <section>
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold lowercase">the teacher</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">
        I'm Mr. Auch. I teach US History, Hidden History, and Beyond the Scoreboard. My room is relaxed on purpose.
        We joke around, chase strange questions, argue over what really happened, and somehow cover a ridiculous amount
        of history along the way.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        The goal is not to make school feel more like school. It is to make the story interesting enough that you want
        to know what happens next. If you leave class laughing and accidentally remember why Reconstruction failed or
        how television changed sports, that works for me.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-2">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold lowercase">the site</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">
        The Desk keeps the slides, games, source packets, class tools, and odd detours in one place. Google Classroom
        still handles assignments, grades, and turn-ins.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-2">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold lowercase">contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Students and families can reach me through Google Classroom or my school email.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-2">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold lowercase">quick answers</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
        <details class="surface-link rounded-lg border border-line bg-white px-4 py-3 open:border-accent">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none font-semibold lowercase">are grades posted here?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-soft">No. Grades, assignments, and turn-ins are in Google Classroom.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="surface-link rounded-lg border border-line bg-white px-4 py-3 open:border-accent">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none font-semibold lowercase">is hidden history a conspiracy-theory class?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
            It is a class about finding out which extraordinary stories are documented, which fall apart, and which
            remain honestly unproven. Watergate, MKUltra, and COINTELPRO sit beside famous hoaxes for a reason.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="surface-link rounded-lg border border-line bg-white px-4 py-3 open:border-accent">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none font-semibold lowercase">where are the latest updates?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-soft">
            Check <a href="/announcements/" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4">announcements</a> for the
            newest additions to the site.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
